      "content": "Here is the comprehensive API reference for the `POST /v1/compute/instance/provision` endpoint, designed to meet strict documentation standards by explicitly documenting every schema property with descriptions, types, and constraints.\n\n### Provisioning Instance\n\nCreates a new compute instance by provisioning resources within the specified region using the provided image and storage configuration.\n\n#### Request Body\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | : |\n| `region` | **string** | **Yes** | The target cloud region where the instance should be launched. Identifiers must match the available zone configurations within your project. |\n| `instance_type` | **string** | **Yes** | The compute tier specification defining CPU, memory, and throughput capabilities. Supported formats include `t2.micro`, `t3.small`, and custom custom-iam instances. |\n| `image_id` | **string** | **Yes** | The unique repository identifier for the operating system image template to use as the base boot volume. UPE image IDs follow the standard format `os-...`. |\n| `storage_gb` | **integer** | No | The allocated size of the attached root volume",
